uctory sections listing the personal pronouns, demonstrative pronouns, and case markers for each language.This sourcebook thus fills a critical need in surveying the languages of a single large area in an island of Southeast Asia. Many language communities in this region are endangered and likely to disappear as functioning entities within the next generation or two; this book may be the only record we will ever have of their existence. Linguists and those with an interest in Austronesian languages will appreciate the breadth and detail that illuminate the linguistic scene in an area where before there had been only pinpoints of light.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2021) 0aAustronesian languageszMalaysiazSabah. 0aAustronesian languageszMalaysiazSarawak. 7aFOREIGN LANGUAGE STUDY / Southeast Asian Languages (see also Vietnamese).2bisacsh1 aBlust, Robert A., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2016z978311070100508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUHP eBook Package 2014-2016z978311056413608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Hawaii Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311066323540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978082485782040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780824857820423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780824857820.jpg  a978-3-11-056413-6  UHP eBook Package 2014-2016c2014d2016  a978-3-11-066323-5  University of Hawaii Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  a978-3-11-070100-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK